title.narrative: OUTPUT 3.4: SYSTEMS STRENGTHENING - HIV-AIDS AND CHILD PROTECTION

description.narrative: Output 3.4: Social welfare, justice systems and schools, at national level and in target counties have improved capacities. with skilled workforce and adequate budgets to prevent, detect, refer and care for girls and boys who are victims of violence, abuse and exploitation and including those are living with HIV, which contributes to Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 3 - Children and adolescents are increasingly protected from exposure to HIV and AIDS, violence, abuse, exploitation and harmful cultural practices, and benefit from increased access to prevention, care, treatment, support, justice and other services needed to ensure their physical, mental and social wellbeing.
